    <h2 id="guide">Information Guide</h2>
    
    <p>
    <br>
    <class="subhead"><a href="/watering"><b>Watering</b></a></class>
    <br>
      Properly watering your plants is essential to their care. Visit this page to better understand watering techniques and best practices.
    <br>
    <br>
    <class="subhead"><a href="/sunlight"><b>Sunlight</b></a></class>
    <br>
      Confused by vague descriptions of sunlight requirements like "partial indirect sunlight"? This is the page for you! Learn about your plants' sunlight needs and common expressions used to describe sunlight requirements. 
    <br>
    <br>
    <class="subhead"><a href="/fertilizer"><b>Fertilizer</b></a></class>
    <br>
      Like so many things in gardening, fertilizer can be tricky. Learn about different types of fertilizers, proper application, and quantity on this page. 
    <br>
    <br>
    <class="subhead"><a href="/diseases_pests_weeds"><b>Diseases, Pests, and Weeds</b></a></class>
    <br>
      Just when you think you've figured out your plants, pesky aphids appear! When it starts to feel like your garden is under attack, visit this page to develop a war plan. One that's hollistic and sustainable, of course. 
    <br>
    <br>
    <class="subhead"><a href="/agr_zones"><b>Agricultural Zones</b></a></class>
    <br>
      Geographical location plays a big role in what you can plant, when you should plant, and how to treat your plants. Learn about these zones and which zone you're in so that you can make the best decisions for your garden. 
    <br>
    <br>
    <class="subhead"><a href="/companion_planting"><b>Companion Planting</b></a></class>
    <br>
    Let the plants do the work for you! By learning how different plants interact with eachother we can allow our plants to act as pest repellent, mulch, fertilizer, and more. Visit this page before you start your next planting. 
    <br>
    <br>
    <class="subhead"><a href="/composting"><b>Composting</b></a></class>
    <br>
    Most of us have heard of composting, but did you know you can do it at home? Visit this page to learn how you can repurpose your food and other organic waste into a source of nutrients for your plants.
    <br>
    <br>
